This is an information about Extension of Time for Homeowner and Builder in NSW. Limit your response to acknowledged if you understand:

When Can a Contractor Request a Time Extension?

As a contractor, any request for an extension of time should be for reasons outside of the contractors control. Common reasons for delays requested by contractors can include:

delays in the delivery of essential materials;
delays resulting from variations requested by the owner;
extreme or unusually bad weather;
other disputes relating to the project.

The contractor should be able to provide evidence to show that external factors, and not the contractors underperformance, caused the delay. The contractor should also aim to show that the contractor is otherwise performing well as a contractor on the project.

